messages.id:
Command line interface for Horizon agent. Most of the sub-commands use the Horizon Agent API at the default location http://localhost (see environment Environment Variables section to override this).

Subcommands Description:
  agbot: List and manage Horizon agreement bot resources.
  agreement: List or manage the active or archived agreements this edge node has made with a Horizon agreement bot.
  architecture: Show the architecture of this machine (as defined by Horizon and golang). 
  attribute: List or manage the global attributes that are currently registered on this Horizon edge node.
  deploycheck: Check deployment compatibility.
  dev: Development tools for creation of services.
  env: Show the Horizon Environment Variables.
  eventlog: List the event logs for the current or all registrations.
  exchange: List and manage Horizon Exchange resources.
  key: List and manage keys for signing and verifying services. 
  metering: List or manage the metering (payment) information for the active or archived agreements.
  mms: List and manage Horizon Model Management Service resources.
  node: List and manage general information about this Horizon edge node.
  policy: List and manage policy for this Horizon edge node. 
  reginput: Create an input file template for this pattern that can be used for the 'hzn register' command (once filled in). 
            This examines the services that the specified pattern uses, and determines the node owner input that is required for them. 
  register: Register this edge node with the management hub.
  service: List or manage the services that are currently registered on this Horizon edge node.
  status: Display the current horizon internal status for the node.
  unregister: Unregister and reset this Horizon edge node so that it is ready to be registered again.
  userinput: List or manager the service user inputs that are currently registered on this Horizon edge node.
  util: Utility commands.
  version: Show the Horizon version.
  voucher: List and manage Horizon SDO ownership vouchers.

Environment Variables:
  HORIZON_URL:  Override the URL at which hzn contacts the Horizon Agent API.
      This can facilitate using a remote Horizon Agent via an ssh tunnel.
  HZN_EXCHANGE_URL:  Override the URL that the 'hzn exchange' sub-commands use
      to communicate with the Horizon Exchange, for example
      https://exchange.bluehorizon.network/api/v1. (By default hzn will ask the
      Horizon Agent for the URL.)
  HZN_ORG_ID:  Default value for the 'hzn exchange -o' flag,
      to specify the organization ID'.
  HZN_EXCHANGE_USER_AUTH:  Default value for the 'hzn exchange -u' or 'hzn
	  register -u' flag, in the form '[org/]user:pw'. Notice that HZN_ORG_ID can be set
	  if org is omitted when HZN_EXCHANGE_USER_AUTH is set.
  HZN_FSS_CSSURL:  Override the URL that the 'hzn mms' sub-commands use
      to communicate with the Horizon Model Management Service, for example
      https://exchange.bluehorizon.network/css/. (By default hzn will ask the
      Horizon Agent for the URL.)
  HZN_SDO_SVC_URL:  Override the URL that the 'hzn sdo' sub-commands use
	  to communicate with SDO owner services. (By default hzn will ask the
		Horizon Agent for the URL.)

  All these environment variables and ones mentioned in the command help can be
  specified in user's configuration file: ~/.hzn/hzn.json with JSON format.
  For example:
  {Com____}

  HZN_EXCHANGE_USER_AUTH:  Default value for the 'hzn exchange -u' or 'hzn
	  register -u' flag, in the form '[org/]user:pw'. Notice that HZN_ORG_ID can be set
	  if org is omitted when HZN_EXCHANGE_USER_AUTH is set.
  HZN_FSS_CSSURL:  Override the URL that the 'hzn mms' sub-commands use
      to communicate with the Horizon Model Management Service, for example
      https://exchange.bluehorizon.network/css/. (By default hzn will ask the
      Horizon Agent for the URL.)
  HZN_SDO_SVC_URL:  Override the URL that the 'hzn sdo' sub-commands use
	  to communicate with SDO owner services. (By default hzn will ask the
		Horizon Agent for the URL.)

  All these environment variables and ones mentioned in the command help can be
  specified in user's configuration file: ~/.hzn/hzn.json with JSON format.
  For example:
  {Com____}
messages.translation:
Command line interface for Horizon agent. Most of the sub-commands use the Horizon Agent API at the default location http://localhost (see environment Environment Variables section to override this).

Subcommands Description:
  agbot: List and manage Horizon agreement bot resources.
  agreement: List or manage the active or archived agreements this edge node has made with a Horizon agreement bot.
  architecture: Show the architecture of this machine (as defined by Horizon and golang). 
  attribute: List or manage the global attributes that are currently registered on this Horizon edge node.
  deploycheck: Check deployment compatibility.
  dev: Development tools for creation of services.
  env: Show the Horizon Environment Variables.
  eventlog: List the event logs for the current or all registrations.
  exchange: List and manage Horizon Exchange resources.
  key: List and manage keys for signing and verifying services. 
  metering: List or manage the metering (payment) information for the active or archived agreements.
  mms: List and manage Horizon Model Management Service resources.
  node: List and manage general information about this Horizon edge node.
  policy: List and manage policy for this Horizon edge node. 
  reginput: Create an input file template for this pattern that can be used for the 'hzn register' command (once filled in). 
            This examines the services that the specified pattern uses, and determines the node owner input that is required for them. 
  register: Register this edge node with the management hub.
  service: List or manage the services that are currently registered on this Horizon edge node.
  status: Display the current horizon internal status for the node.
  unregister: Unregister and reset this Horizon edge node so that it is ready to be registered again.
  userinput: List or manager the service user inputs that are currently registered on this Horizon edge node.
  util: Utility commands.
  version: Show the Horizon version.
  voucher: List and manage Horizon SDO ownership vouchers.

Environment Variables:
  HORIZON_URL:  Override the URL at which hzn contacts the Horizon Agent API.
      This can facilitate using a remote Horizon Agent via an ssh tunnel.
  HZN_EXCHANGE_URL:  Override the URL that the 'hzn exchange' sub-commands use
      to communicate with the Horizon Exchange, for example
      https://exchange.bluehorizon.network/api/v1. (By default hzn will ask the
      Horizon Agent for the URL.)
  HZN_ORG_ID:  Default value for the 'hzn exchange -o' flag,
      to specify the organization ID'.
  HZN_EXCHANGE_USER_AUTH:  Default value for the 'hzn exchange -u' or 'hzn
	  register -u' flag, in the form '[org/]user:pw'. Notice that HZN_ORG_ID can be set
	  if org is omitted when HZN_EXCHANGE_USER_AUTH is set.
  HZN_FSS_CSSURL:  Override the URL that the 'hzn mms' sub-commands use
      to communicate with the Horizon Model Management Service, for example
      https://exchange.bluehorizon.network/css/. (By default hzn will ask the
      Horizon Agent for the URL.)
  HZN_SDO_SVC_URL:  Override the URL that the 'hzn sdo' sub-commands use
	  to communicate with SDO owner services. (By default hzn will ask the
		Horizon Agent for the URL.)

  All these environment variables and ones mentioned in the command help can be
  specified in user's configuration file: ~/.hzn/hzn.json with JSON format.
  For example:
  {Com____}

messages.id: Horizon project containing the definition of a dependency. Mutually exclusive with -s -o --ver -a and --url.
messages.message: Horizon project containing the definition of a dependency. Mutually exclusive with -s -o --ver -a and --url.
messages.translation: Projeto do Horizon que contém a definição de uma dependência. Mutuamente exclusivo com -s -o --ver -a e --url.

messages.id: Horizon Exchange user credentials to query exchange resources. The default is HZN_EXCHANGE_USER_AUTH environment variable. If you don't prepend it with the user's org, it will automatically be prepended with the value of the HZN_ORG_ID environment variable.
messages.message: Horizon Exchange user credentials to query exchange resources. The default is HZN_EXCHANGE_USER_AUTH environment variable. If you don't prepend it with the user's org, it will automatically be prepended with the value of the HZN_ORG_ID environment variable.
messages.translation: As credenciais do usuário do Horizon Exchange para consultar recursos do Exchange. O padrão é a variável de ambiente HZN_EXCHANGE_USER_AUTH. Se o valor não for prefixado com a organização do usuário, ele será automaticamente prefixado com o valor da variável de ambiente HZN_ORG_ID.

messages.id: File containing user input values for configuring the new dependency. If omitted, the userinput file in the dependency project will be used.
messages.message: File containing user input values for configuring the new dependency. If omitted, the userinput file in the dependency project will be used.
messages.translation: Arquivo que contém valores de entrada do usuário para a configuração de uma nova dependência. Se omitido, será usado o arquivo de entrada do usuário no projeto de dependência.

messages.id: List all dependencies.
messages.message: List all dependencies.
messages.translation: Listar todas as dependências.

messages.id: Remove a project dependency.
messages.message: Remove a project dependency.
messages.translation: Remover uma dependência de projeto.

messages.id: For working with a service project.
messages.message: For working with a service project.
messages.translation: Para trabalhar com um projeto de serviço.

messages.id: Show the container/system logs for a service.
messages.message: Show the container/system logs for a service.
messages.translation: Mostrar os logs do contêiner/sistema para um serviço.

messages.id: The name of the service whose log records should be displayed. The service name is the same as the url field of a service definition.
messages.message: The name of the service whose log records should be displayed. The service name is the same as the url field of a service definition.
messages.translation: O nome do serviço cujos registros de log devem ser exibidos. O nome do serviço é o mesmo que o campo de url de uma definição de serviço.

messages.id: (DEPRECATED) This flag is deprecated and is replaced by -c.
messages.message: (DEPRECATED) This flag is deprecated and is replaced by -c.
messages.translation: (DESCONTINUADO) Esta sinalização foi descontinuada e substituída por -c.

messages.id: The name of the service container whose log records should be displayed. Can be omitted if the service definition has only one container in its deployment config.
messages.message: The name of the service container whose log records should be displayed. Can be omitted if the service definition has only one container in its deployment config.
messages.translation: O nome do contêiner de serviço cujos registros de log devem ser exibidos. Pode ser omitido se a definição de serviço tiver apenas um contêiner em sua configuração de implementação.

messages.id: Continuously polls the service's logs to display the most recent records, similar to tail -F behavior.
messages.message: Continuously polls the service's logs to display the most recent records, similar to tail -F behavior.
messages.translation: Pesquisa continuamente os logs do serviço para exibir os registros mais recentes, semelhantes ao comportamento do rodapé -F.

messages.id: Create a new service project.
messages.message: Create a new service project.
messages.translation: Criar um novo projeto de serviço.

messages.id: The Org id that the service is defined within. If this flag is omitted, the HZN_ORG_ID environment variable is used.
messages.message: The Org id that the service is defined within. If this flag is omitted, the HZN_ORG_ID environment variable is used.
messages.translation: O ID da organização na qual o serviço está definido. Se essa sinalização for omitida, a variável de ambiente HZN_ORG_ID será usada.

messages.id: The name of the service. If this flag and the -i flag are omitted, only the skeletal horizon metadata files will be generated.
messages.message: The name of the service. If this flag and the -i flag are omitted, only the skeletal horizon metadata files will be generated.
messages.translation: O nome do serviço. Se essa sinalização e a sinalização -i forem omitidas, somente os arquivos de metadados da estrutura de tópicos do Horizon serão gerados.

messages.id: The version of the service. If this flag is omitted, '0.0.1' is used.
messages.message: The version of the service. If this flag is omitted, '0.0.1' is used.
messages.translation: A versão do serviço. Se essa sinalização for omitida, '0.0.1' será usado.

messages.id: The docker container image base name without the version tag for the service. This command will add arch and version to the base name to form the final image name. The format is 'basename_arch:serviceversion'. This flag can be repeated to specify multiple images when '--noImageGen' flag is specified. This flag is ignored for the '--dconfig {KUBEDEPLOYMENTCONFIGTYPE}' deployment configuration.
messages.message: The docker container image base name without the version tag for the service. This command will add arch and version to the base name to form the final image name. The format is 'basename_arch:serviceversion'. This flag can be repeated to specify multiple images when '--noImageGen' flag is specified. This flag is ignored for the '--dconfig {KUBEDEPLOYMENTCONFIGTYPE}' deployment configuration.
messages.translation: O nome base da imagem do contêiner do Docker sem a tag de versão para o serviço. Esse comando incluirá o arch e a versão no nome base para formar o nome da imagem final. O formato é 'basename_arch:serviceversion'. Essa sinalização pode ser repetida para especificar várias imagens quando a sinalização '--noImageGen' for especificada. Essa sinalização é ignorada para a configuração de implementação '--dconfig {KUBEDEPLOYMENTCONFIGTYPE}'.

messages.id: Indicates that the image is built somewhere else. No image sample code will be created by this command. If this flag is not specified, files for generating a simple service image will be created under current directory.
messages.message: Indicates that the image is built somewhere else. No image sample code will be created by this command. If this flag is not specified, files for generating a simple service image will be created under current directory.
messages.translation: Indica que a imagem foi construída em algum outro lugar. Nenhum código de amostra de imagem será criado por este comando. Se essa sinalização não for especificada, os arquivos para a geração de uma imagem de serviço simples serão criados no diretório atual.

messages.id: Indicates no pattern definition file will be created.
messages.message: Indicates no pattern definition file will be created.
messages.translation: Indica que nenhum arquivo de definição padrão será criado.

messages.id: Indicate no policy file will be created.
messages.message: Indicate no policy file will be created.
messages.translation: Indica que nenhum arquivo de políticas será criado.

messages.id: Indicates the type of deployment configuration that will be used, native (the default), or {KUBEDEPLOYMENTCONFIGTYPE}. This flag can be specified more than once to create a service with more than 1 kind of deployment configuration.
messages.message: Indicates the type of deployment configuration that will be used, native (the default), or {KUBEDEPLOYMENTCONFIGTYPE}. This flag can be specified more than once to create a service with more than 1 kind of deployment configuration.
messages.translation: Indica o tipo de configuração de implementação que será usado, nativo (o padrão) ou {KUBEDEPLOYMENTCONFIGTYPE}. Essa sinalização pode ser especificada mais de uma vez para criar um serviço com mais de 1 tipo de configuração de implementação.

messages.id: Run a service in a mocked Horizon Agent environment. This command is not supported for services using the {KUBEDEPLOYMENTCONFIGTYPE} deployment configuration.
messages.message: Run a service in a mocked Horizon Agent environment. This command is not supported for services using the {KUBEDEPLOYMENTCONFIGTYPE} deployment configuration.
messages.translation: Executar um serviço em um ambiente simulado do Horizon Agent. Esse comando não é suportado para serviços usando a configuração de implementação {KUBEDEPLOYMENTCONFIGTYPE}.

messages.id: File containing user input values for running a test. If omitted, the userinput file for the project will be used.
messages.message: File containing user input values for running a test. If omitted, the userinput file for the project will be used.
messages.translation: Arquivo que contém valores de entrada do usuário para a execução de um teste. Se omitido, será usado o arquivo de entrada de usuário do projeto.

messages.id: File to be made available through the sync service APIs. This flag can be repeated to populate multiple files.
messages.message: File to be made available through the sync service APIs. This flag can be repeated to populate multiple files.
messages.translation: Arquivo a ser disponibilizado por meio das APIs do serviço de sincronização. Essa sinalização pode ser repetida para preencher vários arquivos.

messages.id: The type of file to be made available through the sync service APIs. All config files are presumed to be of the same type. This flag is required if any configFiles are specified.
messages.message: The type of file to be made available through the sync service APIs. All config files are presumed to be of the same type. This flag is required if any configFiles are specified.
messages.translation: O tipo de arquivo a ser disponibilizado por meio das APIs do serviço de sincronização. Presume-se que todos os arquivos de configuração sejam do mesmo tipo. Essa sinalização é necessária caso sejam especificados configFiles.

messages.id: Do not bring up file sync service (FSS) containers. They are brought up by default.
messages.message: Do not bring up file sync service (FSS) containers. They are brought up by default.
messages.translation: Não ativar contêineres do serviço de sincronização de arquivo (FSS). Eles são ativados por padrão.

messages.id: Horizon Exchange user credentials to query exchange resources. Specify it when you want to automatically fetch the missing dependent services from the Exchange. The default is HZN_EXCHANGE_USER_AUTH environment variable. If you don't prepend it with the user's org, it will automatically be prepended with the value of the HZN_ORG_ID environment variable.
messages.message: Horizon Exchange user credentials to query exchange resources. Specify it when you want to automatically fetch the missing dependent services from the Exchange. The default is HZN_EXCHANGE_USER_AUTH environment variable. If you don't prepend it with the user's org, it will automatically be prepended with the value of the HZN_ORG_ID environment variable.
messages.translation: As credenciais do usuário do Horizon Exchange para consultar recursos do Exchange. Especifique quando desejar buscar automaticamente os serviços dependentes ausentes por meio do Exchange. O padrão é a variável de ambiente HZN_EXCHANGE_USER_AUTH. Se o valor não for prefixado com a organização do usuário, ele será automaticamente prefixado com o valor da variável de ambiente HZN_ORG_ID.

messages.id: Filepath of a file containing a secret that is required by the service or one of its dependent services. The filename must match a secret name in the service definition. The file is encoded in JSON as an object containing two keys both typed as a string; "key" is used to indicate the kind of secret, and "value" is the string form of the secret. This flag can be repeated.
messages.message: Filepath of a file containing a secret that is required by the service or one of its dependent services. The filename must match a secret name in the service definition. The file is encoded in JSON as an object containing two keys both typed as a string; "key" is used to indicate the kind of secret, and "value" is the string form of the secret. This flag can be repeated.
messages.translation: Caminho do arquivo de um arquivo contendo um segredo que é requerido pelo serviço ou um de seus serviços dependentes. O nome do arquivo deve corresponder a um nome de segredo na definição de serviço. O arquivo é codificado em JSON como um objeto contendo duas chaves digitadas como uma sequência; "key" é usado para indicar o tipo de segredo, e "value" é a forma de sequência do segredo. Esta sinalização pode ser repetida.

messages.id: Stop a service that is running in a mocked Horizon Agent environment. This command is not supported for services using the {KUBEDEPLOYMENTCONFIGTYPE} deployment configuration.
messages.message: Stop a service that is running in a mocked Horizon Agent environment. This command is not supported for services using the {KUBEDEPLOYMENTCONFIGTYPE} deployment configuration.
messages.translation: Parar um serviço que está em execução em um ambiente simulado do Horizon Agent. Esse comando não é suportado para serviços usando a configuração de implementação {KUBEDEPLOYMENTCONFIGTYPE}.

messages.id: Validate the project for completeness and schema compliance.
messages.message: Validate the project for completeness and schema compliance.
messages.translation: Validar o projeto em relação à integridade e conformidade do esquema.

messages.id: File containing user input values for verification of a project. If omitted, the userinput file for the project will be used.
messages.message: File containing user input values for verification of a project. If omitted, the userinput file for the project will be used.
messages.translation: O arquivo que contém valores de entrada do usuário para a verificação de um projeto. Se omitido, será usado o arquivo de entrada de usuário do projeto.

messages.id: Show the Horizon Environment Variables.
messages.message: Show the Horizon Environment Variables.
messages.translation: Mostrar as variáveis de ambiente do Horizon.

messages.id: List the event logs for the current or all registrations.
messages.message: List the event logs for the current or all registrations.
messages.translation: Listar os logs de eventos para o registro atual ou todos os registros.

messages.id: Continuously polls the event log to display the most recent records, similar to tail -F behavior.
messages.message: Continuously polls the event log to display the most recent records, similar to tail -F behavior.
messages.translation: Pesquisa continuamente o log de eventos para exibir os registros mais recentes, semelhante ao comportamento de cauda -F.

messages.id: List all the event logs including the previous registrations.
messages.message: List all the event logs including the previous registrations.
messages.translation: Listar os logs de eventos, incluindo os registros anteriores.

messages.id: List event logs with details.
messages.message: List event logs with details.
messages.translation: Listar logs de eventos com detalhes.

messages.id: Selection string. This flag can be repeated which means 'AND'. Each flag should be in the format of attribute=value, attribute~value, "attribute>value" or "attribute<value", where '~' means contains. The common attribute names are timestamp, severity, message, event_code, source_type, agreement_id, service_url etc. Use the '-l' flag to see all the attribute names.
messages.message: Selection string. This flag can be repeated which means 'AND'. Each flag should be in the format of attribute=value, attribute~value, "attribute>value" or "attribute<value", where '~' means contains. The common attribute names are timestamp, severity, message, event_code, source_type, agreement_id, service_url etc. Use the '-l' flag to see all the attribute names.
messages.translation: Sequência de seleção. Essa sinalização pode ser repetida, o que significa 'AND'. Cada sinalização deve estar no formato attribute=value, attribute~value, "attribute>value" ou "attribute<value", em que '~' significa conter. Os nomes de atributos comuns são timestamp, severity, message, event_code, source_type, agreement_id, service_url etc. Use a sinalização '-l' para ver todos os nomes de atributos.

messages.id: List all the active errors that will be shared with the Exchange if the node is online.
messages.message: List all the active errors that will be shared with the Exchange if the node is online.
messages.translation: Liste todos os erros ativos que serão compartilhados com o Exchange se o nó estiver on-line.

messages.id: List the full event logs of the surface errors.
messages.message: List the full event logs of the surface errors.
messages.translation: Listar os logs de eventos completos dos erros exibidos.

messages.id: List and manage Horizon Exchange resources.
messages.message: List and manage Horizon Exchange resources.
messages.translation: Listar e gerenciar recursos do Horizon Exchange.

messages.id: Horizon Exchange user credentials to query and create exchange resources. If not specified, HZN_EXCHANGE_USER_AUTH will be used as a default. If you don't prepend it with the user's org, it will automatically be prepended with the -o value. As an alternative to using -o, you can set HZN_ORG_ID with the Horizon exchange organization ID
messages.message: Horizon Exchange user credentials to query and create exchange resources. If not specified, HZN_EXCHANGE_USER_AUTH will be used as a default. If you don't prepend it with the user's org, it will automatically be prepended with the -o value. As an alternative to using -o, you can set HZN_ORG_ID with the Horizon exchange organization ID
messages.translation: As credenciais do usuário do Horizon Exchange para consultar e criar recursos do Exchange. Se não especificado, HZN_EXCHANGE_USER_AUTH será usado como padrão. Se o valor não for prefixado com a organização do usuário, ele será automaticamente prefixado com o valor -o. Como uma alternativa ao uso de -o, é possível configurar HZN_ORG_ID com o ID da organização do Horizon Exchange

messages.id: List and manage agbots in the Horizon Exchange
messages.message: List and manage agbots in the Horizon Exchange
messages.translation: Listar e gerenciar agbots no Horizon Exchange

messages.id: Add this deployment policy to the list of policies this agbot is serving. Currently only support adding all the deployment policies from an organization.
messages.message: Add this deployment policy to the list of policies this agbot is serving. Currently only support adding all the deployment policies from an organization.
messages.translation: Inclua esta política de implementação na lista de políticas que este robô de contrato está servindo. Atualmente, suporta somente a inclusão de todas as políticas de implementação de uma organização.

messages.message: The agbot to add the deployment policy to.
messages.translation: O robô de contrato no qual incluir a política de implementação.

messages.message: Add this pattern to the list of patterns this agbot is serving.
messages.translation: Incluir este padrão na lista de padrões que este agbot está servindo.

messages.translation: O agbot para o qual incluir o padrão.

messages.translation: A organização do padrão a ser incluído.

messages.id: The name of the pattern to add.

messages.translation: O nome do padrão a ser incluído.

messages.message: The organization of the nodes that should be searched. Defaults to patternorg.
messages.translation: A organização dos nós que devem ser procurados. Padronizado como patternorg.

messages.id: Display the agbot resources from the Horizon Exchange.
messages.message: Display the agbot resources from the Horizon Exchange.
messages.translation: Exibir os recursos do agbot a partir do Horizon Exchange.

messages.id: List just this one agbot.
messages.message: List just this one agbot.
messages.translation: Listar apenas este único agbot.

messages.id: When listing all of the agbots, show the entire resource of each agbots, instead of just the name.
messages.message: When listing all of the agbots, show the entire resource of each agbots, instead of just the name.
messages.translation: Ao listar todos os agbots, mostrar o recurso inteiro de cada agbot, em vez de apenas o nome.

messages.id: Display the deployment policies that this agbot is serving.
messages.message: Display the deployment policies that this agbot is serving.
messages.translation: Exiba as políticas de implementação que este robô de contrato está servindo.

messages.id: The agbot to list serving deployment policies for.
messages.message: The agbot to list serving deployment policies for.
messages.translation: O robô de contrato para o qual listar as políticas de implementação que ele está servindo.

messages.id: Display the patterns that this agbot is serving.
messages.message: Display the patterns that this agbot is serving.
messages.translation: Exibir os padrões que este agbot está servindo.

messages.id: The agbot to list the patterns for.
messages.message: The agbot to list the patterns for.
messages.translation: O agbot para o qual listar padrões.

messages.id: The organization of the 1 pattern to list.

messages.translation: A organização do padrão a ser listado.

messages.id: The name of the 1 pattern to list.
messages.message: The name of the 1 pattern to list.

messages.message: Remove this deployment policy from the list of policies this agbot is serving. Currently only support removing all the deployment policies from an organization.
messages.translation: Remova esta política de implementação da lista de políticas que este robô de contrato está servindo. Atualmente, suporta somente a remoção de todas as políticas de implementação de uma organização.

messages.id: The agbot to remove the deployment policy from.
messages.message: The agbot to remove the deployment policy from.
messages.translation: O robô de contrato do qual remover a política de implementação.

messages.id: The organization of the deployment policy to remove.
messages.message: The organization of the deployment policy to remove.
messages.translation: A organização da política de implementação a ser removida.

messages.id: Remove this pattern from the list of patterns this agbot is serving.
messages.message: Remove this pattern from the list of patterns this agbot is serving.
messages.translation: Remover este padrão da lista de padrões que este agbot está servindo.

messages.id: The agbot to remove the pattern from.

messages.translation: O agbot do qual remover o padrão.

messages.translation: A organização do padrão a ser removido.

messages.translation: O nome do padrão a ser removido.

messages.id: List all public services/patterns in all orgs that have orgType: IBM.
messages.message: List all public services/patterns in all orgs that have orgType: IBM.
messages.translation: Listar todos os serviços/padrões públicos em todas as organizações que tenham orgType: IBM.

messages.message: Display all public patterns in all orgs that have orgType: IBM.
messages.translation: Exibir todos os padrões públicos em todas as organizações que tenham orgType: IBM.

messages.translation: Exibir apenas nomes de organizações (IBM) e padrões.

messages.translation: Exibir uma saída detalhada sobre padrões públicos em todas as organizações que possuem orgType: IBM.

messages.translation: Exibir todos os serviços públicos em todas as organizações que tenham orgType: IBM.

messages.translation: Exibir apenas nomes de organizações (IBM) e serviços.

messages.id: Display detailed output about public services in all orgs that have orgType: IBM.
messages.message: Display detailed output about public services in all orgs that have orgType: IBM.
messages.translation: Exibir uma saída detalhada sobre serviços públicos em todas as organizações que possuem orgType: IBM.

messages.id: List and manage deployment policies in the Horizon Exchange.
messages.message: List and manage deployment policies in the Horizon Exchange.
messages.translation: Liste e gerencie políticas de implementação no Horizon Exchange.

messages.id: Add or replace a deployment policy in the Horizon Exchange. Use 'hzn exchange deployment new' for an empty deployment policy template.
messages.message: Add or replace a deployment policy in the Horizon Exchange. Use 'hzn exchange deployment new' for an empty deployment policy template.
messages.translation: Incluir ou substituir uma política de implementação no Horizon Exchange. Use 'hzn exchange deployment new' para um modelo de política de implementação vazio.

messages.id: The Horizon ID and password of the user.
messages.message: The Horizon ID and password of the user.
messages.translation: O ID e a senha do usuário do Horizon.

messages.id: The name of the policy to add or overwrite.
messages.message: The name of the policy to add or overwrite.
messages.translation: O nome da política a ser incluída ou sobrescrita.

messages.id: The path of a JSON file containing the metadata necessary to create/update the service policy in the Horizon Exchange. Specify -f- to read from stdin.
messages.message: The path of a JSON file containing the metadata necessary to create/update the service policy in the Horizon Exchange. Specify -f- to read from stdin.
messages.translation: O caminho de um arquivo JSON que contém os metadados necessários para criar/atualizar a política de serviço no Horizon Exchange. Especifique -f- para ler a partir de stdin.

messages.id: Allow this deployment policy to be published even though it does not have any constraints.
messages.message: Allow this deployment policy to be published even though it does not have any constraints.
messages.translation: Permita que esta política de implementação seja publicada mesmo que não tenha nenhuma restrição.

messages.id: Display the deployment policies from the Horizon Exchange.
messages.message: Display the deployment policies from the Horizon Exchange.
messages.translation: Exiba as políticas de implementação por meio do Horizon Exchange.

messages.id: Display detailed output about the deployment policies.
messages.message: Display detailed output about the deployment policies.
messages.translation: Exiba a saída detalhada sobre as políticas de implementação.

messages.id: List just this one policy. Use <org>/<policy> to specify a public policy in another org, or <org>/ to list all of the public policies in another org.
messages.message: List just this one policy. Use <org>/<policy> to specify a public policy in another org, or <org>/ to list all of the public policies in another org.
messages.translation: Listar apenas esta única política. Use <org>/<policy> para especificar uma política pública em outra organização ou <org>/ para listar todas as políticas públicas em outra organização.

messages.id: Display an empty deployment policy template that can be filled in.
messages.message: Display an empty deployment policy template that can be filled in.
messages.translation: Exibir um modelo de política de implementação vazio que possa ser preenchido.

messages.id: Remove the deployment policy in the Horizon Exchange.
messages.message: Remove the deployment policy in the Horizon Exchange.
messages.translation: Remova a política de implementação no Horizon Exchange.

messages.id: Skip the 'are you sure?' prompt.
messages.message: Skip the 'are you sure?' prompt.
messages.translation: Ignorar a parte 'Tem certeza?' .

messages.id: The name of the deployment policy to be removed.
messages.message: The name of the deployment policy to be removed.
messages.translation: O nome da política de implementação a ser removida.

messages.id: Update one attribute of an existing policy in the Horizon Exchange. The supported attributes are the top level attributes in the policy definition as shown by the command 'hzn exchange deployment new'.
messages.message: Update one attribute of an existing policy in the Horizon Exchange. The supported attributes are the top level attributes in the policy definition as shown by the command 'hzn exchange deployment new'.
messages.translation: Atualizar um atributo de uma política existente no Horizon Exchange. Os atributos suportados são os atributos de nível superior na definição de política, conforme mostrado pelo comando 'hzn exchange deployment new'.

messages.id: The name of the policy to be updated in the Horizon Exchange.
messages.message: The name of the policy to be updated in the Horizon Exchange.
messages.translation: O nome da política a ser atualizada no Horizon Exchange.

messages.id: The path to the json file containing the updated deployment policy attribute to be changed in the Horizon Exchange. Specify -f- to read from stdin.

messages.id: The path of public key file (that corresponds to the private key) that should be stored with the pattern, to be used by the Horizon Agent to verify the signature. If both this and -k flags are not specified, the environment variable HZN_PUBLIC_KEY_FILE will be used. If HZN_PUBLIC_KEY_FILE is not set, ~/.hzn/keys/service.public.pem is the default. If -k is specified and this flag is not specified, then no public key file will be stored with the pattern. The Horizon Agent needs to import the public key to verify the signature.
messages.message: The path of public key file (that corresponds to the private key) that should be stored with the pattern, to be used by the Horizon Agent to verify the signature. If both this and -k flags are not specified, the environment variable HZN_PUBLIC_KEY_FILE will be used. If HZN_PUBLIC_KEY_FILE is not set, ~/.hzn/keys/service.public.pem is the default. If -k is specified and this flag is not specified, then no public key file will be stored with the pattern. The Horizon Agent needs to import the public key to verify the signature.
messages.translation: O caminho do arquivo de chave pública (que corresponde à chave privada) que deve ser armazenado com o padrão, a ser usado pelo Horizon Agent para verificar a assinatura. Se esse item e as sinalizações -k não forem especificados, a variável de ambiente HZN_PUBLIC_KEY_FILE será usada. Se HZN_PUBLIC_KEY_FILE não for configurado, ~/.hzn/keys/service.public.pem será o padrão. Se -k for especificado e essa sinalização não for especificada, nenhum arquivo de chave pública será armazenado com o padrão. O Horizon Agent precisa importar a chave pública para verificar a assinatura.

messages.id: List just this one service. Use <org>/<svc> to specify a public service in another org, or <org>/ to list all of the public services in another org.
messages.message: List just this one service. Use <org>/<svc> to specify a public service in another org, or <org>/ to list all of the public services in another org.
messages.translation: Listar apenas este único serviço. Use <org>/<svc> para especificar um serviço público em outra organização ou <org>/ para listar todos os serviços públicos em outra organização.

messages.id: When listing all of the services, show the entire service definition, instead of just the name. When listing a specific service, show more details.
messages.message: When listing all of the services, show the entire service definition, instead of just the name. When listing a specific service, show more details.
messages.translation: Ao listar todos os serviços, mostre a definição de serviço inteira, em vez de apenas o nome. Ao listar um serviço específico, mostre mais detalhes.

messages.id: The name of the file where the cluster deployment operator yaml archive will be saved. This flag is only used when listing a specific service. This flag is ignored when the service does not have a clusterDeployment attribute.

messages.translation: O nome do arquivo no qual o archive yaml do operador de implementação de cluster será salvo. Esta sinalização é usada somente ao listar um serviço específico. Esta sinalização é ignorada quando o serviço não tem um atributo clusterDeployment.

messages.id: Skip the 'do you want to overwrite?' prompt when -f is specified and the file exists.
messages.message: Skip the 'do you want to overwrite?' prompt when -f is specified and the file exists.
messages.translation: Ignore o prompt 'deseja sobrescrever?' quando -f for especificado e o arquivo existir.

messages.translation: O ID de serviço. Use <org>/<svc> para especificar um serviço de uma organização diferente.

messages.id: Sign and create/update the service resource in the Horizon Exchange.
messages.message: Sign and create/update the service resource in the Horizon Exchange.
messages.translation: Assinar e criar/atualizar o recurso de serviço no Horizon Exchange.

messages.id: The path of a JSON file containing the metadata necessary to create/update the service in the Horizon exchange. See {Sampledir}/service.json and {Sampledir_1}/service_cluster.json. Specify -f- to read from stdin.
messages.message: The path of a JSON file containing the metadata necessary to create/update the service in the Horizon exchange. See {Sampledir}/service.json and {Sampledir_1}/service_cluster.json. Specify -f- to read from stdin.
messages.translation: O caminho de um arquivo JSON que contém os metadados necessários para criar/atualizar o serviço no Horizon Exchange. Consulte {Sampledir}/service.json e {Sampledir_1}/service_cluster.json. Especifique -f- para ler a partir de stdin.

messages.id: The path of a private key file to be used to sign the service. If not specified, the environment variable HZN_PRIVATE_KEY_FILE will be used. If none of them are set, ~/.hzn/keys/service.private.key is the default.
messages.message: The path of a private key file to be used to sign the service. If not specified, the environment variable HZN_PRIVATE_KEY_FILE will be used. If none of them are set, ~/.hzn/keys/service.private.key is the default.
messages.translation: O caminho de um arquivo de chave privado a ser usado para assinar o serviço. Se não especificado, a variável de ambiente HZN_PRIVATE_KEY_FILE será usada. Caso nenhum dos dois seja especificado, ~/.hzn/keys/service.private.key será o padrão.

messages.id: The path of public key file (that corresponds to the private key) that should be stored with the service, to be used by the Horizon Agent to verify the signature. If both this and -k flags are not specified, the environment variable HZN_PUBLIC_KEY_FILE will be used. If HZN_PUBLIC_KEY_FILE is not set, ~/.hzn/keys/service.public.pem is the default. If -k is specified and this flag is not specified, then no public key file will be stored with the service. The Horizon Agent needs to import the public key to verify the signature.
messages.message: The path of public key file (that corresponds to the private key) that should be stored with the service, to be used by the Horizon Agent to verify the signature. If both this and -k flags are not specified, the environment variable HZN_PUBLIC_KEY_FILE will be used. If HZN_PUBLIC_KEY_FILE is not set, ~/.hzn/keys/service.public.pem is the default. If -k is specified and this flag is not specified, then no public key file will be stored with the service. The Horizon Agent needs to import the public key to verify the signature.
messages.translation: O caminho do arquivo de chave pública (que corresponde à chave privada) que deve ser armazenado com o serviço, a ser usado pelo Horizon Agent para verificar a assinatura. Se esse item e as sinalizações -k não forem especificados, a variável de ambiente HZN_PUBLIC_KEY_FILE será usada. Se HZN_PUBLIC_KEY_FILE não for configurado, ~/.hzn/keys/service.public.pem será o padrão. Se -k for especificado e essa sinalização não for especificada, nenhum arquivo de chave pública será armazenado com o serviço. O Horizon Agent precisa importar a chave pública para verificar a assinatura.

messages.id: The image paths in the deployment field have regular tags and should not be changed to sha256 digest values. The image will not get automatically uploaded to the repository. This should only be used during development when testing new versions often.
messages.message: The image paths in the deployment field have regular tags and should not be changed to sha256 digest values. The image will not get automatically uploaded to the repository. This should only be used during development when testing new versions often.
messages.translation: Os caminhos da imagem no campo de implementação possuem tags regulares e não devem ser alterados para valores de compilação sha256. A imagem não será automaticamente transferida por upload para o repositório. Isso deve ser usado apenas durante o desenvolvimento, caso novas versões sejam testadas com frequência.

messages.id: Use the image from the image repository. It will pull the image from the image repository and overwrite the local image if exists. This flag is mutually exclusive with -I.
messages.message: Use the image from the image repository. It will pull the image from the image repository and overwrite the local image if exists. This flag is mutually exclusive with -I.
messages.translation: Usar a imagem do repositório de imagem. Isso extrairá a imagem do repositório de imagem e sobrescreverá a imagem local, se existir. Essa sinalização é mutuamente exclusiva com -I.

messages.id: Docker registry domain and auth that should be stored with the service, to enable the Horizon edge node to access the service's docker images. This flag can be repeated, and each flag should be in the format: registry:user:token
messages.message: Docker registry domain and auth that should be stored with the service, to enable the Horizon edge node to access the service's docker images. This flag can be repeated, and each flag should be in the format: registry:user:token
messages.translation: O domínio de registro do Docker e a autenticação que devem ser armazenados com o serviço, para permitir que o nó de borda do Horizon acesse as imagens do Docker do serviço. Essa sinalização pode ser repetida e cada sinalização deve estar no formato: registry:user:token

messages.id: Overwrite the existing version if the service exists in the Exchange. It will skip the 'do you want to overwrite' prompt.
messages.message: Overwrite the existing version if the service exists in the Exchange. It will skip the 'do you want to overwrite' prompt.
messages.translation: Sobrescreva a versão existente, se o serviço existir no Exchange. Isso ignorará o prompt 'deseja sobrescrever'.

messages.id: The path of the service policy JSON file to be used for the service to be published. This flag is optional
messages.message: The path of the service policy JSON file to be used for the service to be published. This flag is optional
messages.translation: O caminho do arquivo JSON da política de serviço a ser usada para o serviço a ser publicado. Essa sinalização é opcional

messages.id: Whether the service is visible to users outside of the organization. This flag is optional. If left unset, the service will default to whatever the metadata has set. If the service definition has also not set the public field, then the service will by default not be public.
messages.message: Whether the service is visible to users outside of the organization. This flag is optional. If left unset, the service will default to whatever the metadata has set. If the service definition has also not set the public field, then the service will by default not be public.
messages.translation: Se o serviço é visível para usuários fora da organização. Este sinalizador é opcional. Se deixado desconfigurado, o serviço será padronizado de acordo com o que foi configurado pelos metadados. Se a definição de serviço também não tiver configurado o campo público, o serviço, por padrão, não será público.

messages.message: The full path of the private key file. Mutually exclusive with -d. If not specified, the environment variable HZN_PRIVATE_KEY_FILE will be used. If none of them are set, ~/.hzn/keys/service.private.key is the default.
